  {
    "client_msg_id": "8cdfab4e-8b28-4f2d-a551-a309c563be08",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "One anecdote here… I was talking recently with a senior mechanical engineer at an oceanographic research institute. We were talking about programming tools, and he mentioned how CAD makes parts of his job so easy he feels like he’s cheating. Things that used to take a lot of careful calculation can now just be quickly whipped up and simulated--he’s effectively offloaded a lot of his mental model onto CAD.",
    "user": "UFB8STN7K",
